30.236962377538074, 120.42909062784557,Xiao Airport Shutdown,https://enigmalabs.io/library/6b5abeb2-ef4f-43ad-a6de-b8c8ecb40815,In July 2010, Xiaoshan Airport in Hangzhou, China, was temporarily shut down after a flight crew reported a twinkling unidentified aerial phenomenon (UAP), prompting diversions and widespread speculation. Despite initial media frenzy and unofficial claims of military involvement, no conclusive identification was ever made, with experts later attributing the sighting to possible aircraft or a missile launch.
